<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="361" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="12" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,474,500]" pageId="12" pageNumber="361">Comments.</emphasis>
As indicated above, Takahashi described this species from specimens taken on leaves of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="361">Heptapleurinum arboricolum</emphasis>
(= 
<taxonomicName box="[451,694,511,537]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Schefflera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="361" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arboricola">
<emphasis box="[451,694,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="361">Schefflera arboricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) at Sozan near Taihoku. Specimens deposited in TARI have the same data as with the original type description, and these specimens are here assumed to be 
<typeStatus box="[1210,1312,547,573]" pageId="12" pageNumber="361">syntypes</typeStatus>
. Takahashi pointed out that this species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1935" box="[610,778,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Smerinthothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heptapleurinus">
<emphasis box="[610,778,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="361">heptapleurinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in two insignificant characters: colour of the leaf galls and shapes of the mouth cone (
<bibRefCitation author="Takahashi, R." box="[448,630,619,645]" pageId="12" pageNumber="361" pagination="339 - 350" refId="ref15341" refString="Takahashi, R. (1937) Descriptions of new Thysanoptera from Formosa, with notes on the species found on the high elevation of the Islands. Tenthredo / Acta Entomologica, I (3), 339 - 350." type="journal article" year="1937">Takahashi 1937</bibRefCitation>
). Our further studies showed that these two species can be distinguished as follows: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takahashi" authorityYear="1937" box="[283,460,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Smerinthothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heptapleuricola">
<emphasis box="[283,460,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="361">heptapleuricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
po setae about 0.5 as long as dorsal length of eyes; pronotal am setae shorter than aa setae; pelta without CPS but with setae present laterally. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1935" box="[927,1095,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Smerinthothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heptapleurinus">
<emphasis box="[927,1095,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="361">heptapleurinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
po setae are longer than eyes; pronotal am setae are longer than aa setae; pelta is with CPS but without setae laterally.
</paragraph>
